<br><br>
In October in the Pyrenees no persistent snow cover existed. In the Alps the snow line was above 1500 m most of the time. Due to the warmer temperature the snow cover was less than normal. In most parts of central and eastern Europe snow was less than usual for October. Only in northern Europe (Sweden, Finland and northern European Russia) the snow cover extent was, at the end of the month, above normal. In Finland most of the country got its first snow at the end of the month. On the last day of October the country's eastern and northern parts had at most around 20 cm of snow. In Sweden the fresh fallen snow melted during the day, only at the end of October snow depth of more than 20 cm was registered. In European Russia at the end of the month the rain changed to snow. In Central Russia the fresh snow depth exceeded 10-15 cm. But soon this snow was melted. Snow even fell in the Crimea. Its depth in the mountain passes reached 30-40 cm.
In Austria in October there was less snow than normal. No snow was observed in mountains below 1000 m and at higher reaches between 1000 and 1500 m only one day with snow cover instead of 2 to 4 days. During the 22 and 23 October, the snow line on the northern side of the Swiss Alps fell to 1000 m and even reached 700 m in the Glarus region.
